The paper deals with a stochastic variant of the packing-type integer linear programming problem, which is a combinatorial optimization problem. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The paper also proposes a general framework of adaptive and non-adaptive algorithms for this problem, which involves analyzing the performance of those algorithms. This suggests that the paper could also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper applies the framework to a variety of stochastic combinatorial optimization problems such as matching, matroid, and stable set problems, which could place it in the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) sub-categories.
